<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/cotd/0706" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/cotd/0706" rel="nofollow">"Card of the Day&#160;— July, 2006"</a>. 2006-07-27<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/cotd/0706" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/cotd/0706" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/cotd/0706</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-30</span>.  "Black removal spells like Terror or Dark Banishing that could take out large-sized creatures historically had the drawback of not being able to affect other black creatures, and sometimes not artifact creatures either. Since then this drawback has been tweaked in many ways that no longer limit the cards to just non-black or non-artifact."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Card+of+the+Day%26nbsp%3B%E2%80%94+July%2C+2006&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2006-07-27&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Fcotd%2F0706&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFBrady_Dommermuth2006">Brady Dommermuth (2006-02-01). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0206#1" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0206#1" rel="nofollow">"Ask Wizards"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0206#1" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0206#1" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0206#1</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-26</span>.  "The particular issue of red's connection to earth and stone has another aspect as well, though. Red has and will continue to have earth/stone-themed cards. But green wants to be connected to earth as well, in the soil sense. So red gives up a few of its 'earth' cards for green's sake."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Ask+Wizards&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Brady+Dommermuth&amp;rft.au=Brady+Dommermuth&amp;rft.date=2006-02-01&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Faskwizards%2F0206%231&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMark_Rosewater2003"><a href="/wiki/Mark_Rosewater" title="Mark Rosewater">Mark Rosewater</a> (2003-08-18). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr85" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr85" rel="nofollow">"The Value of Pie"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr85" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr85" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr85</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-30</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Value+of+Pie&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mark+Rosewater&amp;rft.au=Mark+Rosewater&amp;rft.date=2003-08-18&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Fdaily%2Fmr85&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMark_Rosewater2003"><a href="/wiki/Mark_Rosewater" title="Mark Rosewater">Mark Rosewater</a> (2003-02-17). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr59" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr59" rel="nofollow">"Banned on the Run"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr59" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr59" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr59</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-30</span>.  "Restricting a card makes games more swingy as the variance of drawing the powerful card has a huge impact on the game. We accept the swinginess in Vintage as we want players to have access to all the cards. But in other formats, we err on the side of making the formats a little less luck-based."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Banned+on+the+Run&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mark+Rosewater&amp;rft.au=Mark+Rosewater&amp;rft.date=2003-02-17&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Fdaily%2Fmr59&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <i>Coldsnap</i> is a special exception to the usual rule.</li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFAvi_Flamholz2004">Avi Flamholz (2004-07-13). <a href="http://www.starcitygames.com/php/news/article/7614.html" class="external text" title="http://www.starcitygames.com/php/news/article/7614.html" rel="nofollow">"Money, Proxies, and the Must-Have List&#160;— A Case for Vintage"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.starcitygames.com/php/news/article/7614.html" class="external free" title="http://www.starcitygames.com/php/news/article/7614.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.starcitygames.com/php/news/article/7614.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-30</span>.  "More and more, the larger U.S. Vintage tournaments are unsanctioned and allow growing numbers of proxies (usually five to ten, sometimes unlimited). In fact, I would be hard pressed to find a sanctioned Type 1 tournament (A.K.A. proxy-free) in the last year or so that drew more than thirty people (other than major conventions like GenCon)."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Money%2C+Proxies%2C+and+the+Must-Have+List%26nbsp%3B%E2%80%94+A+Case+for+Vintage&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Avi+Flamholz&amp;rft.au=Avi+Flamholz&amp;rft.date=2004-07-13&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.starcitygames.com%2Fphp%2Fnews%2Farticle%2F7614.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> Proxies are permitted in sanctioned tournaments if a card is damaged or worn in the course of competition, however. They are also permitted in <a href="#Limited" title="">Limited</a> if the opened cards are already damaged.</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFRosewater">Rosewater, Mark (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2009-02-16"><a href="/wiki/2009" title="2009">2009</a>-<a href="/wiki/February_16" title="February 16">02-16</a></span>). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/Article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/mm/26" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/Article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/mm/26" rel="nofollow">"25 Random Things about Magic"</a>. Wizards of the Coast<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/Article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/mm/26" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/Article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/mm/26" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/Article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/mm/26</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-02-16</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=25+Random+Things+about+Magic&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Rosewater&amp;rft.aufirst=Mark&amp;rft.au=Rosewater%2C+Mark&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2009-02-16%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=Wizards+of+the+Coast&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2FMagic%2FMagazine%2FArticle.aspx%3Fx%3Dmtg%2Fdaily%2Fmm%2F26&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Gatherer-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Gatherer_25-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://ww2.wizards.com/gatherer/Index.aspx" class="external text" title="http://ww2.wizards.com/gatherer/Index.aspx" rel="nofollow">"Gatherer"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://ww2.wizards.com/gatherer/Index.aspx" class="external free" title="http://ww2.wizards.com/gatherer/Index.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://ww2.wizards.com/gatherer/Index.aspx</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-02-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Gatherer&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fww2.wizards.com%2Fgatherer%2FIndex.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, the official <i>Magic</i> card database.</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMark_Rosewater2006"><a href="/wiki/Mark_Rosewater" title="Mark Rosewater">Mark Rosewater</a> (2006-02-06). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr214b" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr214b" rel="nofollow">"Coldsnap Q &amp; A"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr214b" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr214b" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr214b</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-30</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Coldsnap+Q+%26+A&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mark+Rosewater&amp;rft.au=Mark+Rosewater&amp;rft.date=2006-02-06&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Fdaily%2Fmr214b&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> shows those 9 languages as of the summer of 2006. <i>Magic</i> was previously printed in <a href="/wiki/Traditional_Chinese" title="Traditional Chinese" class="mw-redirect">Traditional Chinese</a> (used in <a href="/wiki/Taiwan" title="Taiwan">Taiwan</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Korean_language" title="Korean language">Korean</a>, but this stopped after <i><a href="/wiki/Urza%27s_Saga" title="Urza's Saga">Urza's Saga</a></i>, when <a href="/wiki/Simplified_Chinese" title="Simplified Chinese" class="mw-redirect">Simplified Chinese</a> was added, the official language of the <a href="/wiki/People%27s_Republic_of_China" title="People's Republic of China">People's Republic of China</a>. See <a href="http://www.magiclibrary.net/sets.html" class="external text" title="http://www.magiclibrary.net/sets.html" rel="nofollow">www.magiclibrary.net</a> for a language history, albeit one that is not updated any more.</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> "Typically" is used due to a change in card distribution in <i><a href="/wiki/Time_Spiral" title="Time Spiral">Time Spiral</a></i> which allows premium cards of any rarity to replace Common cards instead of cards of their own rarity. See <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr247" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mr247" rel="nofollow">Purple Reign</a> for more information.</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> Tournament Packs contain one more Uncommon and one less Common than would be acquired from three Booster Packs, so they aren't exactly equal.</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/feature/121" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/feature/121" rel="nofollow">"Card Face Redesign FAQ"</a>. 2003-01-20<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/feature/121" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/feature/121" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/feature/121</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-30</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Card+Face+Redesign+FAQ&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2003-01-20&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Ffeature%2F121&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
