<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFJarvis2007">Jarvis, Jeremy (2007-01-01). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0107" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0107" rel="nofollow">"Ask Wizards"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0107" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0107" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0107</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-04-21</span>.  "In the ‘old days’, art descriptions were vague suggestions of images... Neither continuity nor the idea of worldbuilding (creating distinctive and unique worlds and settings) would become issues until some time later."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Ask+Wizards&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Jarvis&amp;rft.aufirst=Jeremy&amp;rft.au=Jarvis%2C+Jeremy&amp;rft.date=2007-01-01&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Faskwizards%2F0107&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFBuehler2003">Buehler, Randy (2003-11-21). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" rel="nofollow">"Flight of Fancy"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-04-21</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Flight+of+Fancy&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Buehler&amp;rft.aufirst=Randy&amp;rft.au=Buehler%2C+Randy&amp;rft.date=2003-11-21&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Fdaily%2Fmc3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFCavotta2005">Cavotta, Matt (2005-09-07). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" rel="nofollow">"The Magic Style Guide"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/daily/mc3</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-04-21</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Magic+Style+Guide&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Cavotta&amp;rft.aufirst=Matt&amp;rft.au=Cavotta%2C+Matt&amp;rft.date=2005-09-07&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Fdaily%2Fmc3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-38"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFChase2002">Chase, Elaine (2002-06-17). <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0602" class="external text" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0602" rel="nofollow">"Ask Wizards"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0602" class="external free" title="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0602" rel="nofollow">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=mtgcom/askwizards/0602</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-02-15</span>.  "While we don't like to completely rule anything out, there currently aren't any plans to repeat the alternate art within a set model. The main reason is that most players recognize cards through the artwork."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Ask+Wizards&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Chase&amp;rft.aufirst=Elaine&amp;rft.au=Chase%2C+Elaine&amp;rft.date=2002-06-17&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wizards.com%2Fdefault.asp%3Fx%3Dmtgcom%2Faskwizards%2F0602&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Magic:_The_Gathering"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39" title="">^</a></b> A notable exception are Basic Land cards, but those are easily identifiable due to the oversized mana symbol in their text boxes.</li>
